text: CUPERTINO UNION SCHOOL DISTRICT
BOARD OF EDUCATION AGENDA
Tuesday, January 22, 2013
The mission of the Cupertino Union School District is to provide a child-centered environment
that cultivates character, fosters academic excellence, and embraces diversity. District
families, community, and staff join as partners to develop creative, exemplary learners with
the skills and enthusiasm to contribute to a constantly changing global society.
Board of Education
Anjali Kausar
Ben Liao

Phyllis Vogel
Superintendent
Wendy Gudalewicz
www.cusdk8.org
We are pleased to provide you with this agenda and cordially invite you to attend all meetings of
the Board of Education.  In the event you wish more detailed information regarding the business
to be reviewed by the Board of Education, you may view/obtain additional meeting materials at
the District Administration Building or at the Board of Education meeting.
Board of Education agendas are publicly posted at the District Office, at each school in session,
and on our website.
Individuals needing special accommodations should contact the Superintendent’s Office in
writing at least two business days prior to the meeting date.
The regular meetings of the Cupertino Union School District Board of Education are generally
held on the second and fourth Tuesday of the month.  For further information, please call
408–252–3000, Extension 200 or visit our website at www.cusdk8.org.
GOALS
Student Achievement:  Provide an intellectually challenging, developmentally appropriate,
standards-based instructional program for each child.
Student Support Services:  Provide resources and programs designed to support students’
diverse academic, social, and emotional needs.
Human Resources:  Attract, develop, and retain a highly competent, effective, and diverse
staff.
Operational Services:  Ensure financial stability and program growth by optimizing the
acquisition and management of financial resources and district assets.
Next Regular Board Meeting is scheduled for February 12, 2013

5. PUBLIC COMMENTS
The public may address the Board on any agenda item and any item not on the agenda.  The Board president will only call
on those who have filled out comment cards before the meeting, and each speaker will be allotted three (3) minutes.  The
Board will not respond or take action on any non-agenda item comments at this time, although the item may be agendized at
a later date (Ed. Code 35145.5).  The comments shall be made from the podium.  In accordance with Government Code
54954.2 – No action or discussion shall be undertaken on any item not appearing on the posted agenda.  The Board shall
limit the total time to 30 minutes.
6. PRESENTATION
6.1  Recognition of Classified Employees Who Earned Permanent Employee Status
Recess:  The Regular Meeting will recess to a reception in honor of Cupertino Union
School District’s Classified Employees Who Earned Permanent Employee Status in
2012.  The meeting will reconvene following the reception.
